<img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1472085 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/IMG_20210711_222724.png" alt="" width="1414" height="778" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/IMG_20210711_222724.png 1414w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/IMG_20210711_222724-1062x584.png 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/IMG_20210711_222724-487x268.png 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/IMG_20210711_222724-974x536.png 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/IMG_20210711_222724-320x176.png 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/IMG_20210711_222724-640x352.png 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/IMG_20210711_222724-600x330.png 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1414px) 100vw, 1414px" />Walks home with N50million worth of prizes After 16 weeks of pulsating vocal performances, Kingdom Kroseide has emerged as the winner of the Nigerian Idol season 6 competition. He has announced the winner after defeating Francis Atela at the grand finale which held at the Africa Magic studios and aired live on Sunday, July 11 During the finale event, both finalists performed songs by Fela Kuti. While Francis sang Yellow Fever, Kingdom rendered Gentleman. Highpoints of the night include performances by the judges and a beautiful rendition of One Hit by Cohbams Asuquo, one of the guest judges on the show alongside Kingdom. Also artists like Patoranking, Ayra Starr, Ice Prince and Chike performed at the event. Patoranking sang Celebrate Me, which he used to pay tribute to Sound Sultan, whose death was announced on Sunday morning. As the winner, Kingdom walked home with the grand prize, which included a cash prize of N30 million, a brand new SUV, a six-track EP recording deal with three music videos included, an all-expense-paid trip to Seychelles, and a weekend getaway to Dubai for two. Other gifts include a wide range of Tecno products, Bigi branded refrigerator plus one year supply of Bigi drinks, and a DSTV Explora fully installed with a premium subscription for 12 months.